newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine Nov industrial output up 12.8 pct - FIEL.
newsitem.headline: Argentine Nov industrial output up 12.8 pct - FIEL.

text.p: Argentina's industrial output was up 12.8 percent in November compared to the same month last year, private consultantants FIEL said Monday.
Output was down 2.3 percent from October, FIEL said.

Output in the first 11 months of 1996 was 4.7 percent higher than in the same period of 1995, FIEL said in its second provisional estimate of industrial output for November. FIEL produces two estimates per month before announcing its final estimate.
FIEL said 17 of 19 sectors measured boosted their output in the first 11 months of 1996, while two declined.
Tractor output grew 91.0 percent and production of white goods rose 55.5 percent.
The only areas to fall were mineral chemical output, down 5.9 percent, and cement production, down 8.8 percent.
FIEL announced last week that its first estimate for November was that industrial output had risen 13.2 percent from the same month last year.
